---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About">
  <header class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>The Audiopheliac is a lifestyle brand built on a real signal chain.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      A project at the intersection of audio, technology, and AI — wrapped around
      <code>theaudiopheliac.com</code> and grounded in the hardware, software, and
      listening discipline of someone who actually runs the rigs reviewed here.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section__head">
      <div>
        <p class="section__eyebrow">What this is</p>
        <h2>Five lanes, one brand.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid--3">
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="cream">Content</h3>
        <p>Long-form posts, product testing, and technical deep-dives that read like field notes — because they are. No moodboards, no listicles, no recycled press release.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="cream">AI integrations</h3>
        <p>Suno Premier with commercial-use rights. Spotify Local Files indexed against the same library Roon serves. Ableton Live 12 Suite for the parts AI doesn't do.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="cream">Affiliate revenue</h3>
        <p>Amazon Associates store <code>veterananalyt-20</code>. Gear we run, with the receipts to back it. PA-API access pending qualifying sales; Best Buy Developer is the drop-in alternative.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="cream">Music releases</h3>
        <p>AI-assisted productions under <a href="https://suno.com/@audiopheliac" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@audiopheliac</a>, mastered for streaming, released under the Audiopheliac name with commercial rights.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="cream">Storefront (planned)</h3>
        <p>An Amazon storefront curating the rig — turntables, monitors, interfaces, cables, processing. Built around the actual <a href="/studio">signal chain</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="cream">Credibility foundation</h3>
        <p>Yamaha HS7s + JBL LSR310S. Technics SL-1200MK2 with Ortofon Blue. Yamaha R-N800A and a Pro-Ject Phono Box. M-Audio AIR Hub. The hardware isn't the product — it's the receipt.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <blockquote class="pull">
    "Rock 'n' roll. Deal with it."
    <cite>— Motto, after Bret Easton Ellis, <em>The Rules of Attraction</em></cite>
  </blockquote>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section__head">
      <div>
        <p class="section__eyebrow">Operating principles</p>
        <h2>How we work the room.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid--2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Physical layer first</h3>
        <p>Cross-verify routing and physical connections before any software fix. Gain problems masquerade as routing problems. Routing problems masquerade as latency.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Gain staging before EQ</h3>
        <p>Digital controls (Spotify, Windows) stay at max to preserve resolution through the DAC. Analog controls are set once for healthy levels. The source and the MOTU M4 are the daily volume controls; the MX28 master sits at reference and stays there.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Boost-then-distribute</h3>
        <p>Amplify once at the Rolls MB15b, then split. Splitting before boosting causes weak signal in every zone downstream.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>One assumption explicit</h3>
        <p>If current state is unclear, ask one clarifying question — maximum one — and make the assumption explicit in the recommendation. Defaults: 48 kHz / 24-bit.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section__head">
      <div>
        <p class="section__eyebrow">House sound</p>
        <h2>The listening profile.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="lede">
      Country and country-adjacent. Classic rock, hard rock, blues, blues-rock.
      Selective hip-hop. Selective crossover pop. Jazz and classical are not avoided
      out of principle — they're just not the house default. The tracks that land here
      are the ones that reward a hi-fi rig: bass that grounds the room, full low mids,
      lead vocals with body, drums you can feel.
    </p>
    <p class="lede">
      We don't program for crate-digging credibility. We program for the room. Long
      sessions, controlled fatigue, sequenced like a setlist.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="contact">
    <div class="section__head">
      <div>
        <p class="section__eyebrow">Get in touch</p>
        <h2>Contact.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid--2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="cream">Editorial</h3>
        <p>Reviews, technical posts, signal-chain questions, gear leads.</p>
        <p><a href="https://github.com/MarcArmy2003/The-Audiopheliac/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open an issue on GitHub</a> — fastest path. Or <a href="mailto:gillon.marchetti@veterananalytics.com">email</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="cream">Affiliate / sponsorship</h3>
        <p>Gear inquiries, review units, brand partnerships. Subject to <a href="/about#affiliate-policy">affiliate policy</a>.</p>
        <p><a href="mailto:gillon.marchetti@veterananalytics.com">gillon.marchetti@veterananalytics.com</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="affiliate-policy">
    <div class="section__head">
      <div>
        <p class="section__eyebrow">Affiliate policy</p>
        <h2>Receipts before recommendations.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="lede">
      The Audiopheliac participates in the Amazon Associates Program under store ID
      <code>veterananalyt-20</code>. Posts and gear pages include links that may pay a
      small commission on qualifying purchases at no additional cost to the reader.
      Editorial decisions are not made in exchange for those commissions.
    </p>
    <p class="lede">
      Hardware reviewed on the site is hardware that ran — or runs — in the signal
      chains documented on <a href="/studio">/studio</a>. Where a piece is on loan,
      borrowed, or sponsored, it'll say so in plain sight at the top of the post. We
      don't review what we don't run.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-head { padding: var(--sp-6) 0 var(--sp-7); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--surface-edge); margin-bottom: var(--sp-7); }
  .page-head h1 { font-size: clamp(var(--fs-700), 7vw, var(--fs-900)); margin: 0 0 var(--sp-5); max-width: 22ch; }
  code { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--spectrum-1); font-size: 0.92em; }
  .card h3 { margin: 0 0 var(--sp-3); font-size: var(--fs-500); }
  .card p { margin: 0 0 var(--sp-3); color: var(--n-300); }
</style>
